<common-name datatype='string'>gabDTP</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>This transcription unit is part of a complex operon that contains three promoters, two of which are internal. 
&lt;p&gt;
Although [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12446648&quot;&gt;Schneider02&lt;/a&gt;] et al. suggested that the &lt;i&gt;csiR&lt;/i&gt; gene is part of the &lt;i&gt;gabDTP&lt;/i&gt; operon because they saw a polar effect of an insertion in &lt;i&gt;gabT&lt;/i&gt; on &lt;i&gt;gabC&lt;/i&gt;, [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/14731280&quot;&gt;Metzner04&lt;/a&gt;] et al. saw that the presence or absence of the &lt;i&gt;gabD&lt;/i&gt; promoters did not affect the &lt;i&gt;csiR&lt;/i&gt; expression and therefore concluded that the &lt;i&gt;csiR&lt;/i&gt; gene is transcribed in another transcription unit. For this reason, this gene was not included in the operon.
&lt;p&gt;
The &lt;i&gt;gabDTP&lt;/i&gt; operon is induced in response to nitrogen starvation [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/30498244&quot;&gt;Knorr18&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
